have gotten away.

669
00:32:15,308 --> 00:32:17,436
Last night was really busy.

670
00:32:17,436 --> 00:32:20,731
Uh-oh. Big player
just walked in.

671
00:32:20,731 --> 00:32:21,981
Excuse me a minute.

672
00:32:21,981 --> 00:32:23,483
I need to go schmooze.

673
00:32:23,483 --> 00:32:25,277
Okay.

674
00:32:25,277 --> 00:32:27,028
See you later.

675
00:32:27,028 --> 00:32:28,822
Bye.

676
00:32:30,616 --> 00:32:32,743
Hey, I hope you're
still talking to me.

677
00:32:32,743 --> 00:32:35,287
Of course I am.

678
00:32:37,080 --> 00:32:38,415
I got to hand
it to you, Vic.

679
00:32:38,415 --> 00:32:40,041
You've done a great
job with him.

680
00:32:40,041 --> 00:32:41,627
He seems like
a new man.

681
00:32:41,627 --> 00:32:44,504
He just needed
a little time, that's all.

682
00:32:44,504 --> 00:32:46,214
Heals all wounds, right?

683
00:32:48,174 --> 00:32:49,676
Giving him that cane
was a great idea.

684
00:32:49,676 --> 00:32:51,052
I haven't seen him
limp in days.

685
00:32:51,052 --> 00:32:52,429
It gets better.

686
00:32:52,429 --> 00:32:54,389
Yesterday, we drove out
to see the architect

687
00:32:54,389 --> 00:32:56,141
who's designing
the new casino.

688
00:32:56,141 --> 00:32:58,310
I saw him actually
run up a flight of stairs.

689
00:32:58,310 --> 00:32:59,519
No kidding?

690
00:32:59,519 --> 00:33:00,687
Would I kid a kidder?

691
00:33:01,980 --> 00:33:03,690
So what's next for you two?

692
00:33:03,690 --> 00:33:07,653
Ah... we don't break ground
on the casino for about a week

693
00:33:07,653 --> 00:33:10,071
so I thought we'd fly up
to Tahoe for a couple of days.

694
00:33:10,071 --> 00:33:12,282
Sammy's going to be performing
at the Cal-Neva

695
00:33:12,282 --> 00:33:13,951
and I thought I'd introduce
the kid to him.

696
00:33:13,951 --> 00:33:15,327
Sammy's a friend
of yours?

697
00:33:15,327 --> 00:33:16,745
Yeah. We're tight.

698
00:33:18,455 --> 00:33:20,206
I see.

699
00:33:20,206 --> 00:33:21,792
You're going to get
Sammy to convince him

700
00:33:21,792 --> 00:33:23,752
that it's time to
leave the holosuite.

701
00:33:24,753 --> 00:33:26,296
Well... no...

702
00:33:26,296 --> 00:33:27,756
Forget it.

703
00:33:27,756 --> 00:33:29,132
I should know better by now

704
00:33:29,132 --> 00:33:31,301
than to ask you to give
away your secrets.

705
00:33:31,301 --> 00:33:33,762
You probably have the
whole thing mapped out.

706
00:33:33,762 --> 00:33:34,888
I mean, what
am I thinking?

707
00:33:34,888 --> 00:33:36,055
That this new casino

708
00:33:36,055 --> 00:33:38,016
is anything more
than a ploy?

709
00:33:38,016 --> 00:33:39,476
That you'd
actually let him

710
00:33:39,476 --> 00:33:41,979
live out the rest of
his life in a holosuite?

711
00:33:41,979 --> 00:33:43,480
(<i> chuckles</i> )

712
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:44,523
No.

713
00:33:44,523 --> 00:33:45,524
Of course not.

714
00:33:45,524 --> 00:33:46,692
I mean...

715
00:33:46,692 --> 00:33:48,986
the casino's just a...
just a ploy

716
00:33:48,986 --> 00:33:50,696
like you said, you know.

717
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:53,114
They'll be
so glad

718
00:33:53,114 --> 00:33:55,367
to have
him back.

719
00:33:55,367 --> 00:33:56,743
Yeah.

720
00:33:56,743 --> 00:33:59,162
He is better, isn't he?

721
00:33:59,162 --> 00:34:00,455
It's like you said--

722
00:34:00,455 --> 00:34:02,791
he just needed a
break from reality.

723
00:34:02,791 --> 00:34:04,835
Now all that's left
is to decide

724
00:34:04,835 --> 00:34:06,545
when he's ready
to go back.

725
00:34:08,380 --> 00:34:10,382
But I'll leave
that up to you.

726
00:34:10,382 --> 00:34:12,091
See you around.

727
00:34:12,091 --> 00:34:13,593
See ya.

728
00:34:31,194 --> 00:34:32,988
Great set
tonight, Vic.

729
00:34:32,988 --> 00:34:34,406
Thanks.

730
00:34:34,406 --> 00:34:37,034
Lots of familiar
faces in the crowd.

731
00:34:37,034 --> 00:34:39,327
Did I see Rom
and Leeta out there?

732
00:34:39,327 --> 00:34:41,120
They came for a while.

733
00:34:41,120 --> 00:34:43,373
What do you think about
moving the crap tables

734
00:34:43,373 --> 00:34:45,333
over to the south wing

735
00:34:45,333 --> 00:34:48,879
and expanding the slot
machines out into here?

736
00:34:48,879 --> 00:34:50,171
Good idea.

737
00:34:51,548 --> 00:34:53,050
I'll think it over.

738
00:34:53,050 --> 00:34:54,968
But we're supposed
to meet with the architect

739
00:34:54,968 --> 00:34:56,386
tomorrow morning.

740
00:34:56,386 --> 00:34:57,596
Not anymore.

741
00:34:57,596 --> 00:34:58,972
It's time for you
to go, kid.

742
00:34:58,972 --> 00:35:00,473
Go where?

743
00:35:00,473 --> 00:35:01,725
You know where.

744
00:35:01,725 --> 00:35:03,977
It's time to end
the program.

745
00:35:05,478 --> 00:35:07,022
But we've got work to do.

746
00:35:07,022 --> 00:35:08,440
We have a casino to build.

747
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:09,942
No, we don't.

748
00:35:09,942 --> 00:35:11,610
This is just a fantasy.

749
00:35:11,610 --> 00:35:13,612
It's not real.

750
00:35:13,612 --> 00:35:16,073
It's real to me
and it's real to you

751
00:35:16,073 --> 00:35:17,365
and don't say it isn't.

752
00:35:17,365 --> 00:35:18,116
I know better.

753
00:35:18,116 --> 00:35:19,618
You're right.

754
00:35:19,618 --> 00:35:21,286
It's very real to me.

755
00:35:22,328 --> 00:35:24,081
But I'm a hologram, Nog.

756
00:35:24,081 --> 00:35:25,707
I'm not a person.

757
00:35:25,707 --> 00:35:27,918
Until you came along,
I'd never been on

758
00:35:27,918 --> 00:35:30,087
for more than six or
seven hours straight.

759
00:35:30,087 --> 00:35:31,379
I know.

760
00:35:31,379 --> 00:35:33,048
And now you're
running all the time.

761
00:35:33,048 --> 00:35:34,257
Isn't it great?

762
00:35:37,260 --> 00:35:38,845
It's incredible.

763
00:35:39,972 --> 00:35:41,640
Since you've
been here

764
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:45,310
I've slept in a bed every night,
gone to work every day--

765
00:35:45,310 --> 00:35:47,854
had time to read the paper,
play cards with the boys.

766
00:35:47,854 --> 00:35:49,188
I've had a life

767
00:35:49,188 --> 00:35:51,024
and I have
to tell you

768
00:35:51,024 --> 00:35:52,567
it's a precious thing.

769
00:35:52,567 --> 00:35:56,822
I had no idea how much
it means to just... live.

770
00:35:56,822 --> 00:35:59,407
And now I'm going
to return the favor

771
00:35:59,407 --> 00:36:01,159
and give you your life back.

772
00:36:04,537 --> 00:36:07,958
But I don't want that life
anymore, Vic.

773
00:36:07,958 --> 00:36:09,501
I'm perfectly happy here.

774
00:36:09,501 --> 00:36:10,752
What "here"?

775
00:36:10,752 --> 00:36:12,420
There is no "here."

776
00:36:12,420 --> 00:36:14,422
Don't you get it?
This is nowhere.

777
00:36:14,422 --> 00:36:16,424
It's an illusion
and so am I.

778
00:36:16,424 --> 00:36:17,801
In fact,
the only thing

779
00:36:17,801 --> 00:36:19,011
in this entire program

780
00:36:19,011 --> 00:36:20,303
that is not an illusion is you.

781
00:36:20,303 --> 00:36:23,056
Okay. You're right...

782
00:36:23,056 --> 00:36:26,726
but I'm not ready
to go back yet.

783
00:36:26,726 --> 00:36:28,520
I need more time.

784
00:36:31,982 --> 00:36:33,358
So let's just
sleep on this

785
00:36:33,358 --> 00:36:35,110
and talk about it
tomorrow.

786
00:36:35,110 --> 00:36:36,611
Kid...

787
00:36:36,611 --> 00:36:39,197
I hate to do
this to you

788
00:36:39,197 --> 00:36:41,449
but you're not giving
me any choice.

789
00:36:41,449 --> 00:36:42,701
Computer...

790
00:36:42,701 --> 00:36:43,994
No! Don't!

791
00:36:43,994 --> 00:36:45,286
End program.

792
00:37:00,635 --> 00:37:02,054
Oh, hi, Nog.

793
00:37:02,054 --> 00:37:03,055
Chief.

794
00:37:03,055 --> 00:37:04,430
Something wrong?

795
00:37:04,430 --> 00:37:06,850
No, no. I, uh...
I was running

