in Ops

797
00:37:08,309 --> 00:37:09,686
and I noticed a
magnetic flux anomaly

798
00:37:09,686 --> 00:37:10,896
in the holosuite

799
00:37:10,896 --> 00:37:12,564
transilluminator
circuits.

800
00:37:12,564 --> 00:37:13,773
I didn't realize
it was you.

801
00:37:13,773 --> 00:37:15,358
Sorry.

802
00:37:15,358 --> 00:37:16,609
I'm just having trouble

803
00:37:16,609 --> 00:37:18,611
getting the Las Vegas
program to run.

804
00:37:20,697 --> 00:37:22,157
You know...

805
00:37:22,157 --> 00:37:24,534
Vic's matrix is
a little different

806
00:37:24,534 --> 00:37:27,537
than your standard
photokinetic hologram.

807
00:37:27,537 --> 00:37:29,539
He can turn
himself off.

808
00:37:31,041 --> 00:37:32,792
And if he doesn't
want to appear

809
00:37:32,792 --> 00:37:33,960
he doesn't appear.

810
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:35,754
You mean, he has free will?

811
00:37:35,754 --> 00:37:38,090
Hey, I'm an engineer,
not a philosopher.

812
00:37:38,090 --> 00:37:42,177
All I know is, that when Vic
turns himself off, he's off

813
00:37:42,177 --> 00:37:44,179
and ripping out the
guts of the holosuite

814
00:37:44,179 --> 00:37:45,764
isn't going
to change that.

815
00:37:49,642 --> 00:37:51,978
Anything else I
can do for you?

816
00:37:51,978 --> 00:37:53,479
No.

817
00:37:56,858 --> 00:38:00,153
Oh, we, uh... we all
miss you in Ops.

818
00:38:00,153 --> 00:38:01,320
Yeah.

819
00:38:04,699 --> 00:38:06,284
So...

820
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:07,953
now that the Chief's told you

821
00:38:07,953 --> 00:38:09,662
I'm smarter
than the average bear

822
00:38:09,662 --> 00:38:11,664
will you stop messing around
with my holosuite?

823
00:38:11,664 --> 00:38:13,750
If you turn the program back on.

824
00:38:13,750 --> 00:38:16,377
What is it I'm not making
clear to you, Charlie?

825
00:38:16,377 --> 00:38:17,462
You got to go.

826
00:38:19,047 --> 00:38:21,340
Don't you get it?

827
00:38:21,340 --> 00:38:23,176
I can't go out there.

828
00:38:23,176 --> 00:38:25,262
Why not?

829
00:38:27,555 --> 00:38:29,808
I'm scared... okay?

830
00:38:29,808 --> 00:38:31,726
I'm scared.

831
00:38:38,608 --> 00:38:40,860
When the war began...

832
00:38:40,860 --> 00:38:43,780
I wasn't<i> happy</i> or anything

833
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:46,158
but I was eager.

834
00:38:47,993 --> 00:38:50,703
I wanted to test myself.

835
00:38:50,703 --> 00:38:55,458
I wanted to prove I had
what it took to be a soldier

836
00:38:55,458 --> 00:38:59,004
and I saw
a lot of combat.

837
00:38:59,004 --> 00:39:01,631
I saw a lot of people get hurt.

838
00:39:03,883 --> 00:39:06,511
I saw a lot of people die

839
00:39:06,511 --> 00:39:08,513
but I didn't think

840
00:39:08,513 --> 00:39:10,515
anything was going
to happen to me

841
00:39:10,515 --> 00:39:11,975
and then, suddenly

842
00:39:11,975 --> 00:39:16,395
Dr. Bashir is telling me
he has to cut my leg off.

843
00:39:18,106 --> 00:39:20,483
I couldn't believe it.

844
00:39:20,483 --> 00:39:23,987
I still
can't believe it.

845
00:39:23,987 --> 00:39:28,783
If I can get shot,
if I can lose my leg

846
00:39:28,783 --> 00:39:31,494
anything can happen to me, Vic.

847
00:39:31,494 --> 00:39:33,830
I could die tomorrow.

848
00:39:36,582 --> 00:39:38,877
I don't know
if I'm ready to face that.

849
00:39:43,631 --> 00:39:47,593
If I stay here, at least I know

850
00:39:47,593 --> 00:39:49,929
what the future
is going to be like.

851
00:39:51,139 --> 00:39:54,934
You stay here,
you're going to die

852
00:39:54,934 --> 00:39:58,980
not all at once,
but little by little.

853
00:39:58,980 --> 00:40:01,983
Eventually, you'll become
as hollow as I am.

854
00:40:03,776 --> 00:40:05,362
You don't seem hollow to me.

855
00:40:05,362 --> 00:40:08,031
Compared to you,
I'm hollow as a snare drum.

856
00:40:08,031 --> 00:40:10,700
Look, kid, I don't
know what's going

857
00:40:10,700 --> 00:40:12,493
to happen to
you out there.

858
00:40:12,493 --> 00:40:14,537
All I can tell you is that...

859
00:40:14,537 --> 00:40:17,540
you've got to play
the cards life deals you.

860
00:40:17,540 --> 00:40:20,668
Sometimes you win,
sometimes you lose.

861
00:40:22,461 --> 00:40:24,339
But at least you're in the game.

862
00:40:39,604 --> 00:40:41,147
(<i> door opens</i> )

863
00:40:44,192 --> 00:40:46,069
(<i> sighs</i> )

864
00:40:58,623 --> 00:40:59,749
Crazy.

865
00:41:00,875 --> 00:41:02,794
ROM:
He seemed happy.

866
00:41:02,794 --> 00:41:04,379
LEETA:
And he's stopped limping.

867
00:41:04,379 --> 00:41:05,546
QUARK:
You're joking.

868
00:41:05,546 --> 00:41:07,632
No. He's a new man.

869
00:41:07,632 --> 00:41:09,134
You should go see him.

870
00:41:09,134 --> 00:41:11,594
I don't think
I'll need to.

871
00:41:20,478 --> 00:41:21,813
Hi.

872
00:41:21,813 --> 00:41:23,315
Hi.

873
00:41:23,315 --> 00:41:25,442
Are you okay?

874
00:41:25,442 --> 00:41:27,693
No...

875
00:41:27,693 --> 00:41:29,404
but I will be.

876
00:41:50,258 --> 00:41:53,136
Computer, run
program Bashir 62.

877
00:41:57,474 --> 00:41:59,434
Hi, kid.

878
00:41:59,434 --> 00:42:00,477
Hey, nice threads.

879
00:42:00,477 --> 00:42:01,519
Thanks.

880
00:42:01,519 --> 00:42:02,561
You back at work?

881
00:42:02,561 --> 00:42:04,814
Limited duty.

882
00:42:04,814 --> 00:42:06,316
Just a couple
hours a day.

883
00:42:06,316 --> 00:42:07,608
How's it feel?

884
00:42:07,608 --> 00:42:09,527
Different.

885
00:42:09,527 --> 00:42:10,945
I feel older.

886
00:42:10,945 --> 00:42:13,239
Happens to the best of us.

887
00:42:13,239 --> 00:42:15,992
I want to thank you
for all that you did for me.

888
00:42:15,992 --> 00:42:17,660
That's not necessary.

889
00:42:17,660 --> 00:42:19,329
You did something
for me, too.

890
00:42:19,329 --> 00:42:20,538
You gave me a chance

891
00:42:20,538 --> 00:42:22,081
to see what it's like
to have a life.

892
00:42:22,081 --> 00:42:24,376
Well, you're going to
have that chance again.

893
00:42:24,376 --> 00:42:26,252
I've made arrangements
with my Uncle Quark

894
00:42:26,252 --> 00:42:27,753
to keep your
program running

895
00:42:27,753 --> 00:42:30,089
26 hours a day
from now on.

896
00:42:30,089 --> 00:42:31,508
What?

897
00:42:31,508 --> 00:42:32,925
It's my gift to you.

898
00:42:32,925 --> 00:42:37,055
Kid... I don't know
what to say.

899
00:42:37,055 --> 00:42:39,265
Just put it
there, pally

900
00:42:39,265 --> 00:42:40,558
and tell me
you'll always

901
00:42:40,558 --> 00:42:42,018
save a seat
for me up front.

902
00:42:42,018 --> 00:42:44,896
It's a deal, and you
can take that to the bank.

903
00:42:44,896 --> 00:42:46,064
(<i> sighing</i> )

904
00:42:46,064 --> 00:42:47,440
Got to go.

905
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:49,025
I'm buying Jake and
Kesha dinner tonight.

906
00:42:49,025 --> 00:42:50,193
Hey.

907
00:42:50,193 --> 00:42:52,237
Try not to overturn
the furniture.

908
00:42:52,237 --> 00:42:53,946
I'll try.

909
00:42:55,407 --> 00:42:57,033
(<i> chuckles</i> )

910
